President Biden delivered a speech at an ironworkers' training center in Upper Marlboro, Maryland, where he signed an executive order aimed at improving federal construction projects. He thanked the ironworkers for their hard work and highlighted the importance of unions in building the middle class and the country. The executive order will utilize project labor agreements to ensure that construction projects are completed efficiently and with high-quality workmanship. It will also prioritize the use of union jobs on federal construction contracts. President Biden emphasized the need to invest in infrastructure and modernize various federal projects across the country. He also mentioned the importance of buying American-made products and supporting American workers. The executive order is expected to create thousands of union jobs and contribute to the safety and cost-effectiveness of federal construction projects.